Japan Purchases Least Milling Wheat in 10 Weeks in Tender

-- B y   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 
2011-06-02T07:47:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/japan-purchases-least-milling-wheat-in-10-weeks-in-tender-1-.html
Japan  bought 112,215 metric tons of
milling wheat from the U.S. and  Canada  in a regular tender today,
the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries said.  It was the smallest purchase since March 24, when the
government bought 103,125 tons. Shipment is set from July 1 to
July 31, Masafumi Otsuka at the ministry’s grain-trade division
said today by phone.  The ministry, which controls overseas purchases and
domestic sales of wheat to stabilize supply, is  Asia ’s largest
buyer as a single entity. It has bought 960,103 tons through
regular tenders this fiscal year, compared with 5.16 million
tons purchased in the year ended March 31.  Details of this week’s tender are listed below:  To contact the reporter on this story:
